This paper is primarily focused on evolutionary artificial neural networks (EANNS), which are a subfield of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms, which are a type of optimization algorithm, and the combination of different learning algorithms, which are topics that fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with the analysis of complex solution spaces, which is a topic in the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper uses chaotic time series data, which is a topic in the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
